wb8foz@skybridge.scl.cwru.edu (David Lesher) writes:

> My memory of this was that the Germans maintained strict radio silence not
> because they thought Enigma was suspect but rather becuse they {rightly}
> feared signal intelligence.

> SI is, roughly, the process of learning things by the presence of signals,
> regardless of their still-unknown content.

What you describe is referred to as Traffic Analysis, and is usually
defined as the study of message externals. Signals Intelligence is a large
domain, of which Traffic Analysis is one sub-set.
